snippet.textDisplay: A lot of home schooled lawyers in the comments. Standardized field sobriety tests are not pass or fail tests. They are tests to designed to show signs of impairment. Unfortunately the way body cams are, you can’t see the officer do the Horizontal Gaze Nystagmus test while checking Jon’s eyes. People don’t realize how good that test is at detecting intoxication. Could the officer enunciated better? Yes. Could he have said let’s use this straight line and place your left foot on it and place your right foot directly in front of your left foot with the back of your right heel touching your left toe? Yes. He also should have said maintain this position and do not start the test until I tell you begin, do you understand? The officer gave his instructions several times and demonstrated the tests. If Jon wasn’t acting a fool in public, he could have drove home without the police being called on him drunk or not. If you’re going to do something illegal, like drinking and driving, it’d be in your best interest not to draw attention to yourself before driving.
